article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- — Jalen Leach and Caleb Fields each scored 17 points and Fairfield beat Saint Peter's 64-62 on Saturday. Leach had seven rebounds for the Stags (15-9, 9-4 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Fields made four 3-pointers and also had three steals. James Johns Jr. finished with 11 points. Roy Clarke led the Peacocks (11-11, 7-6) in scoring, finishing with 21 points, four assists and two steals. Saint Peter's also got 19 points and two steals from Marcus Randolph. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
